  <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
  <blockquote class="not-prose bg-navy/5 border-l-4 border-gold rounded-r-lg p-5 my-8">
    <p class="font-semibold text-navy mb-2">Need a Decanter Centrifuge for Your Project?</p>
    <p class="text-text-light text-sm">Contact Dolphin Centrifuge for rental availability, pricing, and application support. Call <a href="tel:+12485222573">(248) 522-2573</a> or <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/">request a quote</a>.</p>
  </blockquote>

  <!-- Additive Content -->
  <h2 id="program">Industrial Decanter Centrifuge Rental Program</h2>
  <p>Decanter centrifuges are the workhorse of solids-liquid separation. Unlike disc stack separators that handle fine particles and liquid-liquid separation, decanters are designed for high-solids feeds — slurries, sludges, and suspensions where the solid phase can represent 5% to 60% or more of the total volume.</p>
  <p>Renting a decanter centrifuge from Dolphin Centrifuge gives you access to fully rebuilt, production-ready equipment without the capital expenditure. Every rental decanter is rebuilt in our <a href="/industrial-disc-centrifuge-repair/">Warren, Michigan service facility</a> with new bearings, seals, and hard-facing as needed.</p>

  <h3>Available Decanter Models</h3>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Model</th><th>Bowl Diameter</th><th>Throughput</th><th>Typical Applications</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>NX-314</td><td>14 inches</td><td>Up to 40 GPM</td><td>Wastewater sludge, oily water, drilling mud</td></tr>
      <tr><td>NX-418</td><td>18 inches</td><td>Up to 80 GPM</td><td>Municipal sludge, industrial wastewater, oil sludge</td></tr>
      <tr><td>G2-40</td><td>16 inches</td><td>Up to 60 GPM</td><td>High-G dewatering, fine solids, chemical sludge</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CHNX-418</td><td>18 inches</td><td>Up to 80 GPM</td><td>Food-grade, chemical, pharmaceutical</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- Rental Applications -->
  <h2 id="applications">Decanter Rental Applications</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
    <div class="md:w-1/2">
      <p>Our rental decanters serve a wide range of industries and use cases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Wastewater Sludge Dewatering:</strong> Reduce sludge volume by 70–90% before disposal, cutting hauling and landfill costs</li>
        <li><strong>Oily Water Treatment:</strong> Separate free oil from produced water, bilge water, or wash water for compliant discharge</li>
        <li><strong>Crude Oil Recovery:</strong> Recover oil from tank bottoms, pit cleanouts, and drilling waste</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="md:w-1/2">
      <img loading="lazy" src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-rental/WasteWater-Decanter-300.webp" alt="WasteWater Decanter" width="300" height="300" class="rounded-xl" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Industrial Process:</strong> Clarify process liquids, recover valuable solids, or dewater slurries</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency Response:</strong> Rapid deployment for spill cleanup, lagoon closure, or regulatory compliance deadlines</li>
    <li><strong>Pilot Testing:</strong> Run your actual feed material through a full-scale decanter to generate reliable design data before purchasing</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- What's Included -->
  <h2 id="included">What's Included</h2>
  <p>Dolphin Centrifuge rental decanters are delivered as complete, ready-to-operate systems:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Fully rebuilt decanter centrifuge with new bearings, seals, and wear components</li>
    <li>Drive motor, VFD (variable frequency drive), and control panel</li>
    <li>Feed pump and polymer dosing system (if applicable)</li>
    <li>Interconnecting piping and process connections</li>
    <li>Operating manual with recommended parameters for your application</li>
    <li>Remote or on-site startup and commissioning support</li>
    <li>Technical support throughout the rental period</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- Rental Terms -->
  <h2 id="terms">Rental Terms &amp; Pricing</h2>
  <p>We structure rental agreements to fit your project requirements:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Short-Term (1–3 months):</strong> Ideal for project work, pilot testing, or emergency needs</li>
    <li><strong>Long-Term (6–12+ months):</strong> Reduced monthly rates for extended commitments</li>
    <li><strong>Rent-to-Own:</strong> Apply a portion of rental payments toward eventual purchase</li>
    <li><strong>Mobilization:</strong> We coordinate trucking and delivery nationwide</li>
    <li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Rental includes standard equipment coverage</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Rental pricing depends on the model, duration, and application. Contact us at <a href="mailto:sales@dolphincentrifuge.com">sales@dolphincentrifuge.com</a> or <a href="tel:+12485222573">(248) 522-2573</a> for a detailed quote.</p>

  <h3>Need a Disc Stack Separator Instead?</h3>
  <p>If your application involves liquid-liquid separation, fine solids removal, or oil purification, a disc stack centrifuge may be a better fit. See our <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-rental/">disc stack centrifuge rental program</a> for DMPX-series self-cleaning separators.</p>
  <p>Not sure which type you need? Our <a href="/industrial-centrifuge-sample-testing/">sample testing service</a> can determine the optimal centrifuge type and size for your specific material.</p>

  <!-- Decanter Modules Gallery (Legacy) -->
